children.subject: If I also want to find internship next Summer, would 186 help? What should I consider then?

I think if you're interested in AI / ML, it would be much more beneficial to take 188 + 126 instead of 186. I hear that 127 is a lot more relevant, but 126 really builds up your probability intuition (which also greatly supplements 188)

history.content:
Hi I would appreciate it if someone could give me some advice on what classes I should take for the fall semester. I am going to be a junior in the fall, and I am planning on taking 186+188+126+5 unit breadth(for fun, not required). My other workload includes a research, a club that involves web development and I also want to take a technical decal if possible. 

I am also looking to for more research opportunities in AI/ML because I want to go to grad school. 

Looking at my schedule right now, I am leaning toward not taking eecs126, and I am wondering if that impacts anything. I am taking 189 in the spring so I don't know if 126 and 127 are required or recommended. Does anyone have any advice on what I should do? Are 126 and 127 worth it?
history.subject: Class advice for fall semester
